Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @baby cucumber{1} lengthways, then slice it lengthways into thin strips. Stack a handful of the slices at a time and slice them thinly again into matchsticks.

> TIP: This method of preparing veg is called a 'julienne' cut!

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, @rice vinegar{22%milliliters}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a drizzle of @olive oil{} and the @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Set aside to pickle.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @hoisin sauce{32%grams} and two thirds of the @mayonnaise{96%grams}. Set aside.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Crack the @egg{1} into a medium bowl and whisk. Put the @breadcrumbs{50%grams} and @black sesame seeds{10%grams} into another medium bowl, season with the @salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes} total.

Turn every 2-3 mins and adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, clean the plate you used earlier.

Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to the (now empty) plate lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Add the @baby cucumber{1}(trimmed and sliced into thin matchsticks) and remaining mayo to the slaw. Toss to combine.

Just before everything's ready, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread some of the hoisin mayo over the bun bases. Top with the chicken schnitzel and some pickled cucumber slaw, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your craft burgers with the fries and remaining slaw on the side, along with the remaining hoisin mayo for dipping.

Enjoy!